, male holotype AMP67443, female paratype AMP67444, Gravier.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[154,1111,1544,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3126">gnathopoda. Gnathopod 1 carpus elongate about 1.5 times as long as broad, propodus much less massive than that of male, about 1.2 times length of carpus, palm oblique and clearly defined from posterior margin by obtuse angle, dactylus less stout than that of male, greatly overlapping palm. Gnathopod 2 similar to that of male, but basis anterior margin straight, carpus and propodus shorter, propodus palm less oblique.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4675463" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4675463" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4675463/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127" startId="5.[159,175,1340,1362]" targetBox="[164,1117,172,1307]" targetPageId="5">
