<paragraph blockId="5.[159,1116,1419,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127">
<emphasis box="[199,306,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be confused with no other known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[159,240,1451,1475]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Bemlos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[159,240,1451,1475]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127">Bemlos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the characteristic form of the male gnathopod 1 propodus and dactylus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[159,1116,1419,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127">
<emphasis box="[199,328,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="3127">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the dense granulations on the proximal part of the dactylus of the male gnathopod 1.
</paragraph>
